# Platform Posting SOP

## Operating rule
Every post starts as a draft in the content queue. Nothing sensitive gets posted without approval.

## 1) X
### Goal
Short, sharp execution/risk insights and founder momentum.

### Format
- 180-270 characters
- one idea only
- no hype
- no performance promises
- light CTA only

### Post types
- one-line insight
- build-in-public note
- ops lesson
- myth-busting line

### Posting rhythm
- 2 posts per day
- morning insight
- afternoon build note

### Approval check
Block if it mentions:
- guaranteed returns
- monthly profit claims
- exact client result claims

## 2) LinkedIn
### Goal
Trust, seriousness, founder credibility.

### Format
- 120-250 words
- 3-5 short paragraphs
- one technical lesson or operator insight
- no exaggerated CTA

### Post types
- founder lessons
- execution architecture
- risk-control posts
- beta-build updates

### Posting rhythm
- 1 post per day
- best window: morning or early afternoon

### Approval check
Block if it sounds salesy, scammy, or too vague.

## 3) Facebook
### Goal
Repurpose founder updates for broader personal-network visibility.

### Format
- 80-180 words
- simpler than LinkedIn
- more conversational
- no hype

### Post types
- founder build updates
- lessons learned
- beta progress notes
- call for conversations

### Posting rhythm
- 3-5 times per week

### Approval check
Block if the post reads like an investment solicitation.

## 4) Reddit
### Goal
Earn credibility through actual technical insight.

### Format
- plain text
- 120-220 words
- specific technical angle
- no obvious self-promo

### Post types
- monitoring lessons
- rejection/filter logic
- automation architecture
- execution/system-state discussions

### Posting rhythm
- 2-3 times per week max
- manual post only

### Approval check
Block if it reads like marketing copy. Manual posting only.

## 5) Medium
### Goal
Longer-form authority and searchable evergreen content.

### Format
- 600-1200 words
- clear headline
- one deep topic
- strong intro + structured sections

### Post types
- execution system explainers
- kill switch breakdowns
- what most trading bots miss operationally
- founder essays on building under pressure

### Posting rhythm
- 1 article per week

### Approval check
Block unsupported performance language and legal-risk claims.

## 6) Substack
### Goal
Owned audience, direct trust, recurring founder/operator narrative.

### Format
- 500-1200 words
- more personal than Medium
- more direct than LinkedIn
- always useful, never fluffy

### Post types
- weekly operating notes
- architecture breakdowns
- lessons from live refinement
- trust and control layer posts

### Posting rhythm
- 2 short notes per week
- 1 deeper weekly post

### Approval check
Block any post that overstates outcomes or sounds like a signal service.

## Queue workflow
1. Add ops note.
2. Content Agent generates channel-specific drafts.
3. Review all drafts.
4. Approve low-risk drafts.
5. Manually post Reddit.
6. Schedule or post approved X/LinkedIn/Facebook.
7. Publish one longer-form piece to Medium or Substack.
8. Log posted URL back into content queue.
